{
  "stem": "935.9",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "Having a very good time, control came.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And these two guys, one of them lifted me up and took me into one of the rooms.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "It turned out to be the morgue.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "I was spending my first night so-called free in the morgue, where those people who had dysentery had died.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "Man, I was on the same slab with a dead man, in the same sheet, staying there all night long until these Germans for control, which never came for control, only to drink.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "They heard that there was whiskey to be had, so they came up to drink, disappeared.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "And Eva was in another room, also in the morgue, but she slept through the whole thing, because she was drunk anyway.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "The next day, they marched us down, and the Swedish people didn't come.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "And they didn't come, and they didn't come.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "There was-- this was not-- the war had not ended.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "It was about two weeks before the end of the war.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "There was bombing, there was shooting, the Nazis were still marching around.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "We were outside the camp, and we had decided, all of us, we're not going to back in there again.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "Whatever happens, they must come eventually.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "Much, much later, about two days and two nights later, they came. 10 very, very tired men on trucks.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "On old, broken down trucks.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "The Swedish leader with his assistant, and so on.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "And the first time I saw and heard English-- I mean, I've heard English before.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "But I saw an American was outside the concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "The drivers were American boys.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "They had fought in Africa, had been taken prisoners, were exchanged by the Swedish Red Cross against German prisoners, and had volunteered for the Swedish Red Cross to drive and get us out.",
      "word_count": 33
    }
  ],
